We’re rebranding PrestoSQL as Trino 我们将 PrestoSQL 更名为 Trino

Dec 27, 2020 • Martin Traverso, Dain Sundstrom, David Phillips 2020 年 12 月 27 日 • Martin Traverso、Dain Sundstrom、David Phillips

We’re rebranding PrestoSQL as Trino. The software and the community you have come to love and depend on aren’t going anywhere, we are simply renaming. Trino is the new name for PrestoSQL, the project supported by the founders and creators of Presto® along with the major contributors – just under a shiny new name. And now you can find us here:我们将 PrestoSQL 更名为 Trino。您喜爱和依赖的软件和社区不会消失，我们只是在重命名。 Trino 是 PrestoSQL 的新名称，该项目得到了 Presto® 的创始人和创建者以及主要贡献者的支持——只是使用了一个闪亮的新名称。现在您可以在这里找到我们：

  • GitHub: https://github.com/trinodb/trino. Please give it a star!GitHub：https://github.com/trinodb/trino。请给它一个星！
  • Twitter: @trinodb推特：@trinodb
  • Slack: https://trino.io/slack.html松弛：https://trino.io/slack.html

If you want to learn why we’re doing this, read on…如果您想了解我们为什么这样做，请继续阅读……

In 2012, Dain, David and Martin joined the Facebook data infrastructure team. Together with Eric Hwang, we created Presto® to address the problems of low latency interactive analytics over Facebook’s massive Hadoop data warehouse. One of our non-negotiable conditions was for Presto® to be an open source project. Open source is in our DNA - we had all used and participated in open source projects to various degrees in the past, and we recognized the power of open communities and developers coming together to build successful software that can stand the test of time.2012 年，Dain、David 和 Martin 加入了 Facebook 数据基础设施团队。我们与 Eric Hwang 一起创建了 Presto®，以解决 Facebook 庞大的 Hadoop 数据仓库的低延迟交互式分析问题。我们不可协商的条件之一是让 Presto® 成为一个开源项目。开源是我们的 DNA——过去我们都在不同程度上使用和参与过开源项目，我们认识到开放社区和开发人员共同构建经得起时间考验的成功软件的力量。

Over the next six years, we worked hard to build a healthy open source community and ecosystem around the project. We worked with developers and users all over the world and welcomed them into the Presto® community. Presto® was on a path of increasing growth and success, in large part because of the contributions from developers across many fields and all over the world.在接下来的六年里，我们努力围绕该项目建立一个健康的开源社区和生态系统。我们与世界各地的开发人员和用户合作，并欢迎他们加入 Presto® 社区。 Presto® 走上了日益增长和成功的道路，这在很大程度上要归功于来自世界各地许多领域的开发人员的贡献。

Unfortunately in 2018, it became clear that Facebook management wanted to have tighter control over the project and its future. This culminated with their decision to grant Facebook developers commit rights on the project without any prior experience in Presto®. We strongly believe that this kind of decision is not compatible with having a healthy, open community. Moreover, they made this decision by fiat without engaging the Presto® community. As a matter of principle, we had no choice but to leave Facebook in order to focus on making sure Presto® continued to be a successful project with an open, collaborative and independent community. In reality, the choice was easy.不幸的是，在 2018 年，Facebook 管理层显然希望对该项目及其未来进行更严格的控制。这最终导致他们决定授予 Facebook 开发人员对该项目的承诺权利，而无需任何 Presto® 经验。我们坚信，这种决定与拥有一个健康、开放的社区是不相容的。此外，他们在没有与 Presto® 社区接触的情况下通过法令做出了这一决定。原则上，我们别无选择，只能离开 Facebook，以专注于确保 Presto® 继续成为一个成功的项目，拥有一个开放、协作和独立的社区。实际上，选择很容易。

We started the Presto Software Foundation in January 2019 as an independent entity to oversee the development of the software and community, continuing the meritocratic system that had been in place over the previous 6 years. The community quickly consolidated under this new home. We intentionally stayed unemployed over the next 10 months to focus on expanding and strengthening the community by working directly with major users and contributors, as well as reaching out to a wider group of users and developers across the globe. This resulted in new use cases and an injection of energy, making the project more vibrant than ever before as even more new users and developers became engaged. But, don’t take our word for it, let the data speak for itself:我们于 2019 年 1 月成立了 Presto Software Foundation，作为一个独立实体来监督软件和社区的开发，延续了过去 6 年来一直存在的精英制度。社区在这个新家下迅速巩固。我们有意在接下来的 10 个月内保持失业状态，以通过直接与主要用户和贡献者合作以及接触全球更广泛的用户和开发人员群体来专注于扩大和加强社区。这导致了新的用例和能量的注入，随着更多新用户和开发人员的参与，使该项目比以往任何时候都更有活力。但是，不要相信我们的话，让数据说明一切：

Months after this consolidation, Facebook decided to create a competing community using The Linux Foundation®. As a first action, Facebook applied for a trademark on Presto®. This was a surprising, norm-breaking move because up until that point, the Presto® name had been used without constraints by commercial and non-commercial products for over 6 years. In September of 2019, Facebook established the Presto Foundation at The Linux Foundation®, and immediately began working to enforce this new trademark. We spent the better part of the last year trying to agree to terms with Facebook and The Linux Foundation that would not negatively impact the community, but unfortunately we were unable to do so. The end result is that we must now change the name in a short period of time, with little ability to minimize user disruption.合并几个月后，Facebook 决定使用 Linux Foundation® 创建一个竞争社区。作为第一步，Facebook 在 Presto® 上申请了商标。这是一个令人惊讶的、打破常规的举动，因为在此之前，Presto® 名称已经在商业和非商业产品中不受限制地使用了 6 年多。 2019 年 9 月，Facebook 在 The Linux Foundation® 成立了 Presto Foundation，并立即开始努力实施这一新商标。去年的大部分时间里，我们都在努力与 Facebook 和 Linux 基金会达成不会对社区产生负面影响的条款，但不幸的是我们无法这样做。最终结果是我们现在必须在短时间内更改名称，几乎没有能力将用户中断降到最低。

On a personal note, and as the founders who named the project Presto® in the first place, this is an incredibly sad and disappointing turn of events. And while we will always have fondness for the name Presto®, we have come to accept that a name is just a name. To be frank, we’re tired of this endless distraction, and we intend to focus on what matters most and what we are best at doing – building high quality software everyone can rely on and fostering a healthy community of users and developers that build it and support it. We’re not going anywhere – we’re the same people, the same amazing software, under a new name: Trino.就个人而言，作为最初将项目命名为 Presto® 的创始人，这是一个令人难以置信的悲伤和令人失望的事件转折。虽然我们将永远喜欢 Presto® 这个名字，但我们已经开始接受名字只是一个名字。坦率地说，我们厌倦了这种无休止的分心，我们打算专注于最重要的事情和我们最擅长的事情——构建每个人都可以依赖的高质量软件，并培养一个由构建它的用户和开发人员组成的健康社区并支持它。我们不会去任何地方——我们是同一个人，同样出色的软件，只是换了个新名字：Trino。

If you love this project, you already love Trino. ❤️如果您喜欢这个项目，那么您已经喜欢上了 Trino。 ❤️

Facebook is a registered trademark of Facebook Inc. The Linux Foundation and Presto are trademarks of The Linux Foundation.Facebook 是 Facebook Inc. 的注册商标。Linux Foundation 和 Presto 是 The Linux Foundation 的商标。

Migrating from PrestoSQL to Trino 从 PrestoSQL 迁移到 Trino

Jan 4, 2021 • David Phillips, Dain Sundstrom 2021 年 1 月 4 日 • 戴恩·桑德斯特罗姆 (David Phillips)

As we previously announced, we’re rebranding Presto SQL as Trino. Now comes the hard part: migrating to the new version of the software. We just released the first version, Trino 351, which uses the name Trino everywhere, both internally and externally. Unfortunately, there are some unavoidable compatibility aspects that administrators of Trino need to know about. We hope this post makes the transition as smooth as possible.正如我们之前宣布的那样，我们将把 Presto SQL 更名为 Trino。现在是困难的部分：迁移到软件的新版本。我们刚刚发布了第一个版本 Trino 351，它在内部和外部到处都使用 Trino 这个名称。不幸的是，Trino 的管理员需要了解一些不可避免的兼容性问题。我们希望这篇文章能让过渡尽可能顺利。

Things that haven’t changed #没有改变的事情#

Let’s start with the good news. For end users running queries against Trino, everything should be the same. There are no changes to the SQL language, SQL functions, session properties, etc.让我们从好消息开始吧。对于针对 Trino 运行查询的最终用户，一切都应该是相同的。 SQL 语言、SQL 函数、会话属性等没有变化。

Users now see Trino in error messages, a different logo in the web UI, and error stack traces have a different package name, but otherwise they won’t know that anything has changed. All of their views, reports, or other stored queries will work as before.用户现在会在错误消息中看到 Trino，在 Web UI 中看到不同的徽标，并且错误堆栈跟踪具有不同的包名称，但否则他们不会知道任何事情都发生了变化。他们的所有视图、报告或其他存储的查询都将像以前一样工作。

Similarly for administrators, except for a few things noted in the Trino 351 release notes, all the configuration properties are the same.与管理员类似，除了 Trino 351 发行说明中提到的几件事外，所有配置属性都是相同的。

Client protocol compatiblity #客户端协议兼容性#

The client protocol is how clients, such as the CLI or JDBC driver, talk to Trino. It uses standard HTTP as the underlying communications protocol, with some custom HTTP headers to communicate values to and from Trino. Unfortunately, those header names started with X-Presto- and thus had to be changed to X-Trino-.客户端协议是客户端（例如 CLI 或 JDBC 驱动程序）与 Trino 通信的方式。它使用标准的 HTTP 作为底层通信协议，使用一些自定义的 HTTP 标头来与 Trino 交换值。不幸的是，这些标头名称以 X-Presto- 开头，因此必须更改为 X-Trino-。

The Trino CLI and JDBC driver send the new headers, so they are only compatible with Trino versions 351 and newer. Users should wait to upgrade the CLI or JDBC driver until the Trino servers they talk to have been upgraded.Trino CLI 和 JDBC 驱动程序发送新的标头，因此它们仅与 Trino 351 及更新版本兼容。用户应该等待升级 CLI 或 JDBC 驱动程序，直到他们与之交谈的 Trino 服务器已升级。

Out of the box, the Trino server does not work with older clients. However, in order to support a graceful transition, you can allow the server to support older clients by adding a configuration property:开箱即用，Trino 服务器不适用于旧客户端。但是，为了支持优雅的转换，您可以通过添加配置属性允许服务器支持旧客户端：

protocol.v1.alternate-header-name=Presto

We recommend using version 350 of CLI and JDBC driver as the transition version. It has all the newest features such as variable precision timestamps, has been tested with a range of older server versions, and is the last version to support older servers.我们建议使用 350 版的 CLI 和 JDBC 驱动程序作为过渡版本。它具有所有最新功能，例如可变精度时间戳，已经过一系列旧服务器版本的测试，并且是支持旧服务器的最后一个版本。

JDBC driver #JDBC 驱动程序#

The URL prefix for the JDBC driver now starts with jdbc:trino: instead of jdbc:presto:. This means that any client applications using the JDBC driver need to update their connection configuration. The old prefix is still supported, but will be removed in a future release.JDBC 驱动程序的 URL 前缀现在以 jdbc:trino: 开头，而不是 jdbc:presto:。这意味着任何使用 JDBC 驱动程序的客户端应用程序都需要更新它们的连接配置。旧前缀仍然受支持，但将在未来版本中删除。

The class name of the driver is now io.trino.jdbc.TrinoDriver. This is of no concern to most users, as the driver is normally accessed via the standard JDBC auto-discovery mechanism based on the URL. As with the URL prefix, the old name is still supported, but will be removed in a future release.驱动程序的类名现在是 io.trino.jdbc.TrinoDriver。这对大多数用户来说并不重要，因为驱动程序通常是通过基于 URL 的标准 JDBC 自动发现机制访问的。与 URL 前缀一样，旧名称仍受支持，但将在未来版本中删除。

Server RPM #服务器转速 #

The name of the RPM has changed, so it is treated as a different RPM, and thus you cannot simply upgrade from the old version to the new version. All of the directories for the RPM that contained the name presto now use trino instead. You likely want to uninstall the old RPM, rename the config and log directories, then install the new RPM.RPM 的名称已更改，因此它被视为不同的 RPM，因此您不能简单地从旧版本升级到新版本。所有包含名称 presto 的 RPM 目录现在都使用 trino。您可能想要卸载旧的 RPM，重命名配置和日志目录，然后安装新的 RPM。

Docker image #码头工人形象#

The Trino Docker image is now published as trinodb/trino. The supported configuration directory is now /etc/trino. The CLI is now named trino instead of presto.Trino Docker 镜像现在发布为 trinodb/trino。支持的配置目录现在是 /etc/trino。 CLI 现在命名为 trino 而不是 presto。

JMX MBean naming #JMX MBean 命名#

Trino runs on the JVM, which has the JMX framework as a standard way to expose system and application metrics. Trino exposes a huge number of JMX metrics for administrators to monitor their clusters. You might be using these metrics via your monitoring system, or perhaps you are accessing them in SQL via the Trino JMX connector.Trino 在 JVM 上运行，JVM 将 JMX 框架作为公开系统和应用程序指标的标准方式。 Trino 公开了大量的 JMX 指标供管理员监控他们的集群。您可能通过监控系统使用这些指标，或者您可能通过 Trino JMX 连接器在 SQL 中访问它们。

The metrics for Trino server now start with trino instead of presto. You might need to update this name in your monitoring system, or you can revert to the old name:Trino 服务器的指标现在以 trino 而不是 presto 开头。您可能需要在监控系统中更新此名称，或者您可以恢复为旧名称：

jmx.base-name=presto

Similarly, the metrics for the Elasticsearch, Hive, Iceberg, Raptor, and Thrift connectors now start with trino.plugin instead of presto.plugin. Again, you might need to update these names in your monitoring system, or you can revert to the old name. For example, for the Hive connector:同样，Elasticsearch、Hive、Iceberg、Raptor 和 Thrift 连接器的指标现在以 trino.plugin 而不是 presto.plugin 开头。同样，您可能需要在监控系统中更新这些名称，或者您可以恢复为旧名称。例如，对于 Hive 连接器：

jmx.base-name=presto.plugin.hive

Thrift connector #节俭连接器#

The Thrift connector had many backwards incompatible changes to both the Thrift service interface and the configuration properties. You need update all of your implementations of the Thrift service used by the connector.Thrift 连接器对 Thrift 服务接口和配置属性进行了许多向后不兼容的更改。您需要更新连接器使用的 Thrift 服务的所有实现。

SPI #接口#

If you have any custom plugins for Trino, such as connectors or functions, these need to be updated. The package name is now io.trino.spi, and a few classes were renamed:如果您有任何 Trino 的自定义插件，例如连接器或功能，则需要更新这些插件。包名现在是 io.trino.spi，一些类被重命名：

  • PrestoException to TrinoExceptionPrestoException 到 TrinoException
  • PrestoPrincipal to TrinoPrincipalPrestoPrincipal 到 TrinoPrincipal
  • PrestoWarning to TrinoWarningPrestoWarning 到 TrinoWarning

There are no functional changes, so all you should need to do is update your imports and rename the references to the above class names.没有功能上的变化，所以您需要做的就是更新您的导入并将引用重命名为上述类名。

Migration guide #迁移指南#

Now that you understand what is different and what you need to change, you can start thinking about the list of steps needed to perform the migration. The following is a rough plan for upgrading your environment.现在您了解了不同之处和需要更改的内容，您可以开始考虑执行迁移所需的步骤列表。以下是升级环境的粗略计划。

Step 1: Prepare to deploy the new version第一步：准备部署新版本

  • Let users know the name is changing, so they are not surprised by the logo changes in the UI.让用户知道名称正在更改，因此他们不会对 UI 中的徽标更改感到惊讶。
  • Make sure that users are using recent client versions. Ideally, upgrade them all to version 350, as mentioned above. You can check the HTTP request logs for the coordinator to see what client versions are in use.确保用户使用的是最新的客户端版本。理想情况下，如上所述，将它们全部升级到 350 版。您可以检查协调器的 HTTP 请求日志以查看正在使用的客户端版本。
  • Update your server configuration with protocol.v1.alternate-header-name=Presto to allow supporting all of your existing Presto clients.使用 protocol.v1.alternate-header-name=Presto 更新您的服务器配置，以允许支持所有现有的 Presto 客户端。
  • If you are using the RPM, have a plan to deal with the new RPM name and the trino directory names.如果您正在使用 RPM，请计划处理新的 RPM 名称和 trino 目录名称。
  • If you are using Docker, use the new image name, make sure your configuration will be mounted using the trino path name, and remember that the CLI is now named trino.如果您使用的是 Docker，请使用新的映像名称，确保您的配置将使用 trino 路径名称进行挂载，并记住 CLI 现在已命名为 trino。
  • Update any custom plugins to use the new SPI.更新任何自定义插件以使用新的 SPI。
  • Check if you have anything using JMX to monitor your clusters, and decide if you will update them to the new names or set a Trino config to revert to the old names.检查您是否有任何使用 JMX 来监控集群的东西，并决定是否将它们更新为新名称或设置 Trino 配置以恢复为旧名称。

Step 2: Upgrade your servers to Trino 351+第 2 步：将您的服务器升级到 Trino 351+

  • Upgrade development and staging servers.升级开发和登台服务器。
  • Upgrade production servers. If you have multiple clusters, you can do them one at a time, and verify everything is working before moving on to the next one.升级生产服务器。如果您有多个集群，您可以一次一个地执行它们，并在转移到下一个之前验证一切正常。

Step 3: Upgrade clients第 3 步：升级客户端

  • Upgrade all clients including the CLI, JDBC driver, Python, etc., to the Trino versions.将所有客户端，包括 CLI、JDBC 驱动程序、Python 等升级到 Trino 版本。
  • Update any applications using JDBC to use the new jdbc:trino: connection URL prefix.更新任何使用 JDBC 的应用程序以使用新的 jdbc:trino: 连接 URL 前缀。

Step 4: Cleanup第 4 步：清理

  • Remove the protocol.v1.alternate-header-name configuration property.删除 protocol.v1.alternate-header-name 配置属性。
  • If you configured Trino to use the old JMX names, convert your monitoring system to use the new JMX names and remove the fallback configs.如果您将 Trino 配置为使用旧的 JMX 名称，请将您的监控系统转换为使用新的 JMX 名称并删除回退配置。

Getting help #获得帮助#

We’re here to help! If you run into any issues while upgrading, or having any questions or concerns, ask on Slack.我们随时为您提供帮助！如果您在升级时遇到任何问题，或者有任何疑问或疑虑，请在 Slack 上提问。
